{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/change-network-configuration-with-ip-command.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"change-ip\" style=\"position:relative;\">Change IP<a href=\"#change-ip\" aria-label=\"change ip permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Here are the commands used to change the network settings by adding or removing IP addresses and turning on or off network interfaces.</p>\n<p>They can be useful when you want to connect your computer to a different network or when you want to troubleshoot network connectivity issues.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">ip</span> addr del <span class=\"token number\">192.168</span>.1.2/24 dev eno1\n<span class=\"token function\">ip</span> addr <span class=\"token function\">add</span> <span class=\"token number\">192.168</span>.0.2/24 dev eno1\n<span class=\"token function\">ip</span> <span class=\"token function\">link</span> <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">set</span> up dev eno1</code></pre></div>\n<ol>\n<li>Remove the IP address <code class=\"language-text\">192.168.1.2</code> that is assigned to a network interface called <code class=\"language-text\">eno1</code>. The <code class=\"language-text\">/24</code> part is a fancy way of saying that it is a small network (it is equivalent to the <code class=\"language-text\">255.255.255.0</code> network mask).</li>\n<li>Add a new IP address <code class=\"language-text\">192.168.0.2</code> to the same network interface called <code class=\"language-text\">eno1</code>. This is like giving your computer a new phone number that other devices can use to call it.</li>\n<li>Turn on the network interface eno1 so that it can start communicating with other devices on the network. It's like turning on the switch for a light bulb so that it can start working.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"set-default-gateway\" style=\"position:relative;\">Set default gateway<a href=\"#set-default-gateway\" aria-label=\"set default gateway permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">ip</span> route change default via <span class=\"token number\">192.168</span>.0.1 dev eno1</code></pre></div>\n<p>It's like telling your computer to use a specific road to get to your friend's house, \"go through the big park\".</p>","excerpt":"Change IP Here are the commands used to change the network settings by adding or removing IP addresses and turning on or off network…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#change-ip\">Change IP</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#set-default-gateway\">Set default gateway</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"September 02, 2022","published":"September 02, 2022","lastModified":"September 02, 2022","title":"ip command","subtitle":"Change network configuration","section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/change-network-configuration-with-ip-command.md","url":"/linux/change-network-configuration-with-ip-command","next":{"excerpt":"","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/read-cpu-frequency.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Read CPU frequency","date":"2023-04-03T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"5af44ea0-e52d-56a5-8d21-c72dfe1237ae"},"previous":{"excerpt":"In some scenarios when you don't have access to the Docker registry, or limited or no internet, then this approach can be hepful. Save image…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/move-docker-image-between-computers.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Move docker image between computers","date":"2022-09-02T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"25803972-1097-5c93-b9b0-5654d423c4b0"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"Check support Check Treble support with TrebleInfo Treblize Of course Nvidia Shield Tablet doesn't support Treble. But this should be simple…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/unofficial-treble-support-for-nvidia-shield.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Treble for NVIDIA Shield K1","date":"2023-07-07T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"b9de171a-5788-56a9-be71-618453e32b34"},{"excerpt":"I hate Reddit and forums. Especially popular forums like XDA, the source of unique and valuable information and good advice. But. All…","fileAbsolutePath":"/ho